  <h1>Voice Search PPC advertising</h1>

    <p>We are all familiar at least with the concept of PPC (pay per click) advertising. It's the reason why Google is so rich. Each one of us probably sees over a hundred ppc ads a day, most of them without even ralising it. each time that you search for something on Google, 3 or 4 or more ads will be somewhere among the search results (usually right at the top). 

But how does your business get an ad in front of a person when they search using their voice assistant on their cell phone or home speaker device? How can a device give an audible answer that includes 3 or more ads? The short answer is that it can't.

Ads for voice search is a winner-takes-all proposition. Be first or go home.

Let's take a look at how some of the voice search interfaces respond to a voice query and deliver the answers (and ads) to the searcher.</p>

